thread.title: Paxton Eakin

author: Paxton Eakin
title: Paxton Eakin
text: So for starters I was iffy on this service and the cost because it just seemed like a scam. Finally I bit the bullet to unlock. Roughly $140 to have my iPhone 7 unlocked. Website said 2-3 days it took about a week. With that being said it worked. So yes it took longer than advertised but now I'm free to choose whatever network I please and have service when I deploy again. I could not be happier. I heard about this service from a guy I deployed with in 2014. Could not be happier. Expect it to take longer than adverts but it definitely works. Couldn't be happier.
